post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

Have a wonderful evening.

post_text:
Good Evening Parents,
Please review the attached letter regarding COVID-19. Unfortunately, all after school activities and events have been cancelled. This includes Mother-Son BINGO, STEM Club and Reading Night Activities. As more guidance is given, we will continue to communicate it with you.
Please continue practicing best practices that would limit the spread of flu like symptoms, including:
-Get your family vaccinated.
-Stay home if you are sick.
-Cover your moth and nose with a tissue when you cough and sneeze.
-Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds - the time it takes to hum the "Happy Birthday" song twice.
-Clean frequently touched surfaces by using a soap-and-water solution or products with a label that says "EPA-approved". Always follow product direction labels.
text:
Good Evening Parents,
Please review the attached letter regarding COVID-19. Unfortunately, all after school activities and events have been cancelled. This includes Mother-Son BINGO, STEM Club and Reading Night Activities. As more guidance is given, we will continue to communicate it with you.
Please continue practicing best practices that would limit the spread of flu like symptoms, including:
-Get your family vaccinated.
-Stay home if you are sick.
-Cover your moth and nose with a tissue when you cough and sneeze.
-Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds - the time it takes to hum the "Happy Birthday" song twice.
-Clean frequently touched surfaces by using a soap-and-water solution or products with a label that says "EPA-approved". Always follow product direction labels.

post_text: 5th grade students are learning about the Earth's rotation in science. They built their own shadow tracker (sun dial) to measure the length of the shadow throughout the day. The movement of the shadow on their shadow tracker and the length of the shadow should prove that we are rotating even though we can not feel it or see it.

post_text: With Thanksgiving right around the corner, it's the time of year when we think of all the things we are thankful for. It's also a great opportunity to talk about giving back. Flagship's annual Thanksgiving Food Drive began on Monday. We will be collecting nonperishable food items through the month of November in order to help provide those in need with a Thanksgiving Feast! Classes will be competing to see who can bring in the most food items and a reward will be given to the class with the most, by November 25th. If you have any questions, please see Dean Maguire.
